instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get 6.5 quarts of 5W-30 motor oil (synthetic recommended), a new oil filter (Toyota OEM #90915-YZZD3 or equivalent), drain pan, oil filter wrench, 14mm socket for drain plug, and a torque wrench (optional).

instructions.title: Warm Up Engine
instructions.instruction: Run the engine for 5–10 minutes to warm the oil, then shut it off.

instructions.title: Raise Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Use a jack to raise the front of the vehicle and secure it with jack stands on level ground. Ensure the parking brake is engaged.

instructions.title: Locate Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Find the 14mm oil drain plug on the oil pan, usually toward the rear of the engine block. Position the drain pan beneath it.

instructions.title: Drain Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Carefully remove the drain plug and let the oil drain completely. Inspect the gasket and replace it if worn.

instructions.title: Reinstall Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Reinstall the drain plug. Tighten securely, or torque to 27 ft-lbs (37 Nm) if using a torque wrench. Do not overtighten.

instructions.title: Locate Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Locate the oil filter, typically on the driver’s side below the alternator. Place the drain pan beneath the filter.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Use an oil filter wrench to loosen and remove the old filter. Expect some oil to spill.

instructions.title: Prepare New Filter
instructions.instruction: Apply a thin layer of new oil to the rubber gasket of the new filter. Install by hand until snug, then tighten an additional 3/4 turn. Do not use a wrench to overtighten.

instructions.title: Lower Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Safely lower the vehicle from the jack stands.

instructions.title: Open Oil Filler Cap
instructions.instruction: Remove the oil filler cap located on top of the engine.

instructions.title: Add New Oil
instructions.instruction: Pour in about 6 quarts of new 5W-30 oil using a funnel for accuracy.

instructions.title: Run Engine and Check Leaks
instructions.instruction: Replace the oil filler cap, start the engine, and let it run for 1–2 minutes. Check for leaks around the drain plug and filter.

instructions.title: Wait and Recheck Level
instructions.instruction: Shut off the engine and wait 5–10 minutes for oil to settle. Use the dipstick to check oil level.

instructions.title: Top Off if Needed
instructions.instruction: Add oil in small amounts until the dipstick shows the level between the 'low' and 'full' marks. Avoid overfilling.

instructions.title: Dispose of Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Properly dispose of the old oil and filter at an authorized recycling center.

instructions.title: Reset Maintenance Light
instructions.instruction: Turn ignition to ON (engine off). Press and hold the Odometer reset button until the 'MAINT REQD' light turns off (about 10 seconds). Turn ignition off.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Obtain a new 12V automotive battery (Group 24F or specified in owner's manual). Gather 10mm and 13mm wrenches, a battery terminal brush, battery terminal protector spray, baking soda and water solution for cleaning corrosion, rags or paper towels, and wear eye protection and gloves.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off the vehicle, engage the parking brake, set transmission to Park (P), and remove the key from the ignition for safety.

instructions.title: Locate Battery
instructions.instruction: Open the hood and locate the battery, typically on the passenger side of the engine bay.

instructions.title: Disconnect Negative Terminal
instructions.instruction: Using a 10mm wrench, loosen the nut on the negative (-) terminal clamp. Twist and remove the cable, moving it aside to prevent accidental contact.

instructions.title: Disconnect Positive Terminal
instructions.instruction: Using a 10mm wrench, loosen the nut on the positive (+) terminal clamp. Twist and remove the cable, moving it aside from the battery.

instructions.title: Remove Hold-Down Clamp
instructions.instruction: Use a 13mm wrench to loosen the nut on the battery hold-down clamp. Remove the clamp securing the battery.

instructions.title: Remove Old Battery
instructions.instruction: Lift the old battery straight up and out of the tray carefully. Batteries are heavy, so use proper lifting technique or ask for assistance.

instructions.title: Clean Tray and Terminals
instructions.instruction: Inspect the battery tray and clamps for corrosion. Clean with a baking soda and water solution, scrub with a brush, rinse, and dry thoroughly.

instructions.title: Place New Battery
instructions.instruction: Position the new battery in the tray, making sure it sits flat with terminals oriented the same as the old battery.

instructions.title: Secure Battery
instructions.instruction: Reinstall the hold-down clamp and tighten the 13mm nut firmly, ensuring the battery is secure but not overtightened.

instructions.title: Protect Positive Terminal
instructions.instruction: Spray battery terminal protector onto the positive (+) terminal.

instructions.title: Reconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach the positive (+) cable clamp to the positive terminal and tighten the 10mm nut securely.

instructions.title: Protect Negative Terminal
instructions.instruction: Spray battery terminal protector onto the negative (-) terminal.

instructions.title: Reconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach the negative (-) cable clamp to the negative terminal and tighten the 10mm nut securely.

instructions.title: Finish and Test
instructions.instruction: Close the hood and start the vehicle to confirm proper installation. Reset radio presets or other electronics if needed.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new cabin air filter (confirm correct part number for Lexus GX 470). Have a small flathead screwdriver handy if clips need prying.

instructions.title: Empty Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Open the passenger-side glove compartment and remove all contents.

instructions.title: Release Stopper Tabs
instructions.instruction: Locate the two plastic stopper tabs inside the glove compartment (one on each side). Push them inward to allow the glove box to swing down further.

instructions.title: Detach Damper Arm
instructions.instruction: On the right side of the glove box, gently unclip or slide off the damper arm if present, so the glove box can drop fully.

instructions.title: Locate Filter Housing
instructions.instruction: With the glove box lowered or detached, locate the rectangular cabin air filter housing behind it. It will have a plastic cover with clips.

instructions.title: Remove Housing Cover
instructions.instruction: Unclip the two retaining clips on the sides of the filter housing cover and remove the cover.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Slide the old cabin air filter element straight out. Note the airflow arrow direction printed on the filter.

instructions.title: Clean Housing
instructions.instruction: Inspect the housing for debris or leaves and clean as necessary.

instructions.title: Orient New Filter
instructions.instruction: Align the new cabin air filter with the airflow arrow pointing in the same direction as the old filter (typically downward).

instructions.title: Insert New Filter
instructions.instruction: Slide the new filter element fully into the housing until it sits firmly.

instructions.title: Reattach Cover
instructions.instruction: Replace the housing cover and snap the retaining clips securely into place.

instructions.title: Reconnect Damper Arm
instructions.instruction: Reattach the damper arm to the glove compartment if applicable.

instructions.title: Reposition Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Push the glove box back up until the stopper tabs engage, returning it to normal operation.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Close the glove compartment and dispose of the old filter properly.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Obtain a new engine air filter (confirm correct part number for the Lexus GX 470). Have a flathead screwdriver or 10mm socket if your airbox uses screws or bolts.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Ensure the vehicle is turned off and the engine is cool before starting.

instructions.title: Locate Air Filter Housing
instructions.instruction: Open the hood and find the air filter housing. On the GX 470 (4.7L V8), it is usually a large black plastic box on the passenger side of the engine bay, connected to the intake manifold by a tube.

instructions.title: Release Retaining Clips
instructions.instruction: Unclip the 2–4 retaining clips around the air filter housing. If your model uses a screw or bolt, remove it instead.

instructions.title: Open Housing
instructions.instruction: Carefully lift the top half of the air filter housing. It may pivot open on a hinge. Slightly pull away from intake hoses if necessary.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Take out the old, dirty air filter element from the lower half of the housing.

instructions.title: Clean Housing
instructions.instruction: Inspect the air filter housing for leaves, dust, or debris. Wipe it clean with a rag if needed.

instructions.title: Insert New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place the new air filter element into the lower housing, ensuring it fits snugly in the grooves.

instructions.title: Close Housing
instructions.instruction: Align the top half of the housing with the bottom half and press firmly to seal.

instructions.title: Secure Housing
instructions.instruction: Re-engage all retaining clips. Reinstall and tighten any screws or bolts if applicable.

instructions.title: Check Intake Hoses
instructions.instruction: Ensure all intake hoses connected to the airbox are properly secured.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Close the hood to complete the replacement.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Obtain the correct replacement turn signal bulb (e.g., 7440A/7440NA for front or rear, verify via owner's manual or old bulb). Have a small flathead screwdriver ready if clips need prying.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Ensure the vehicle and lights are turned off. Allow any recently used bulbs to cool before handling.

instructions.title: Determine Location
instructions.instruction: Identify if you are replacing a front or rear turn signal bulb, as the access method differs slightly.

instructions.title: Access Front Turn Signal
instructions.instruction: Open the hood. Locate the back of the headlight assembly and find the turn signal bulb socket. You may need to remove a plastic cover or shield for access.

instructions.title: Access Rear Turn Signal
instructions.instruction: Open the rear hatch or trunk. Remove the access panel or unscrew clips/nuts securing the taillight assembly. Carefully pull the assembly away or twist the socket out from behind if accessible.

instructions.title: Remove Bulb Socket
instructions.instruction: Grasp the turn signal bulb socket and twist it counter-clockwise about a quarter turn to unlock. Pull the socket straight out of the housing.

instructions.title: Remove Old Bulb
instructions.instruction: Pull the old bulb straight out of the socket. Wiggle gently if needed. Use caution to avoid breaking the bulb.

instructions.title: Insert New Bulb
instructions.instruction: Insert the new bulb firmly into the socket. Avoid touching the glass with bare hands; use a cloth or gloves.

instructions.title: Test New Bulb
instructions.instruction: Turn on the ignition and activate the turn signal or hazard lights to confirm the bulb is working correctly.

instructions.title: Reinstall Socket
instructions.instruction: Insert the bulb socket back into the housing and twist clockwise to lock it securely in place.

instructions.title: Reassemble
instructions.instruction: Reattach any removed covers, shields, or taillight assemblies. Secure with screws, clips, or nuts as required.

instructions.title: Close Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Close the hood or rear hatch to complete the replacement process.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get new windshield wiper blades (confirm correct lengths for driver and passenger sides, e.g., Driver: 22 inches, Passenger: 20–21 inches for a GX 470). Also have a clean rag or small towel ready.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off the vehicle. For easier access, turn the wipers on once, then switch off the ignition when they stop in the upright position.

instructions.title: Work Safely
instructions.instruction: Work on one wiper at a time to avoid scratching the windshield if a wiper arm snaps down accidentally.

instructions.title: Lift Wiper Arm
instructions.instruction: Lift the wiper arm away from the windshield until it locks into the upright service position. Be careful not to let it snap back onto the glass.

instructions.title: Locate Release Mechanism
instructions.instruction: Find the release mechanism on the old wiper blade. Most GX 470s use a J-hook style with a tab or button to press or lift.

instructions.title: Remove Old Blade
instructions.instruction: Press or lift the tab and slide the old blade down and off the J-hook. Wiggle gently if needed.

instructions.title: Protect Windshield
instructions.instruction: Place a rag or towel on the windshield under the exposed arm to prevent damage if it falls.

instructions.title: Attach New Blade
instructions.instruction: Open the new wiper blade packaging. Hook the J-hook through the opening on the new blade’s attachment point. Pull upward until it clicks securely into place. Check that it’s locked.

instructions.title: Lower Wiper Arm
instructions.instruction: Carefully lower the wiper arm back onto the windshield without snapping it down.

instructions.title: Repeat for Other Side
instructions.instruction: Repeat the same process for the second wiper blade.

instructions.title: Test Wipers
instructions.instruction: Turn on the vehicle and test the wipers to confirm they work properly and clear the windshield effectively.

instructions.title: Warm Up Engine
instructions.instruction: Warm up the engine for a few minutes to help the oil flow more easily.

instructions.title: Lift Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Use a jack to lift the car and secure it with jack stands on a level surface.

instructions.title: Position Drain Pan
instructions.instruction: Place an oil drain pan directly under the oil drain plug.

instructions.title: Drain Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Remove the drain plug and let the oil drain completely into the pan.

instructions.title: Remove Old Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Unscrew and remove the old oil filter, allowing any remaining oil to drain.

instructions.title: Install New Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Install the new oil filter, tightening it by hand until snug.

instructions.title: Reinstall Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Reinsert the drain plug and tighten it securely.

instructions.title: Add New Oil
instructions.instruction: Pour the correct type and amount of new oil into the engine through the oil filler cap.

instructions.title: Check Oil Level
instructions.instruction: Use the dipstick to check the oil level, ensuring it’s between the min and max marks.

instructions.title: Check for Leaks
instructions.instruction: Start the engine and let it run briefly, then inspect for leaks around the drain plug and filter.

instructions.title: Turn Off Engine
instructions.instruction: Turn off the engine and remove the key from the ignition for safety.

instructions.title: Locate Battery
instructions.instruction: Open the hood and locate the vehicle’s battery in the engine compartment.

instructions.title: Disconnect Cables
instructions.instruction: Disconnect the negative (-) cable first, then the positive (+) cable.

instructions.title: Remove Hold-Down Clamp
instructions.instruction: Loosen and remove the battery hold-down clamp that secures the battery in place.

instructions.title: Remove Old Battery
instructions.instruction: Lift the old battery straight up and out of the tray carefully (it may be heavy).

instructions.title: Install New Battery
instructions.instruction: Place the new battery into the tray, ensuring it sits securely.

instructions.title: Reconnect Cables
instructions.instruction: Reconnect the positive (+) cable first, then the negative (-) cable.

instructions.title: Secure Battery
instructions.instruction: Reinstall and tighten the battery hold-down clamp to keep the battery in place.

instructions.title: Test Installation
instructions.instruction: Start the vehicle to verify the new battery is installed and functioning correctly.

instructions.title: Empty Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Open the glove box and remove all its contents.

instructions.title: Release Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Push in the sides of the glove box to release the stops and let it drop down.

instructions.title: Access Filter Compartment
instructions.instruction: Locate the cabin air filter compartment behind the glove box and open the cover.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Pull out the old cabin air filter and discard it.

instructions.title: Insert New Filter
instructions.instruction: Insert the new filter with the airflow arrows pointing downward.

instructions.title: Reattach Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Close the filter compartment cover and reattach the glove box securely.

instructions.title: Locate Air Filter Box
instructions.instruction: Open the hood and locate the air filter box in the engine compartment.

instructions.title: Remove Air Filter Cover
instructions.instruction: Unclip or unscrew the air filter box cover to access the filter.

instructions.title: Remove Old Air Filter
instructions.instruction: Take out the old air filter from the box and set it aside.

instructions.title: Clean Air Filter Box
instructions.instruction: Check inside the air filter box and clean out any dirt or debris.

instructions.title: Insert New Air Filter
instructions.instruction: Place the new air filter into the box, ensuring it sits properly.

instructions.title: Secure Air Filter Cover
instructions.instruction: Reattach the air filter box cover by clipping or screwing it back into place.

instructions.title: Turn Off Engine and Open Hood
instructions.instruction: Turn off the engine and open the hood to access the headlight assembly.

instructions.title: Locate Turn Signal Socket
instructions.instruction: Find the turn signal socket positioned behind the headlight.

instructions.title: Remove Socket
instructions.instruction: Twist and pull out the socket carefully from the headlight housing.

instructions.title: Replace Bulb
instructions.instruction: Remove the old bulb and insert a new one of the correct type.

instructions.title: Reinsert Socket
instructions.instruction: Place the socket back into the housing and twist it to lock securely.

instructions.title: Test Turn Signal
instructions.instruction: Turn on the vehicle’s turn signal to confirm the new bulb works correctly.

instructions.title: Lift Wiper Arms
instructions.instruction: Lift the wiper arms off the windshield and position them upright.

instructions.title: Press Release Tab
instructions.instruction: Locate and press the release tab on the wiper blade to unlock it.

instructions.title: Remove Old Blade
instructions.instruction: Slide the old blade off the hook and set it aside.

instructions.title: Align New Blade
instructions.instruction: Position the new blade so the hook aligns with the attachment point.

instructions.title: Secure New Blade
instructions.instruction: Slide the new blade into place and press until it clicks securely.

instructions.title: Lower Wiper Arms
instructions.instruction: Lower the wiper arms gently back onto the windshield.

instructions.title: Lift the Wiper Arm
instructions.instruction: Lift the wiper arms away from the windshield.

instructions.title: Remove Old Blade
instructions.instruction: Press the tab where the blade meets the arm and slide it off.

instructions.title: Install New Blade
instructions.instruction: Align the new blade and click it into place.

instructions.title: Turn Off the Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Ensure the vehicle is turned off and the keys are removed from the ignition.

instructions.title: Access the Turn Signal Housing
instructions.instruction: Open the hood (for front signals) or trunk (for rear signals) to locate the back of the turn signal housing.

instructions.title: Remove the Bulb Socket
instructions.instruction: Twist the bulb socket counterclockwise and gently pull it out from the housing.

instructions.title: Remove the Old Bulb
instructions.instruction: Pull the old bulb straight out from the socket.

instructions.title: Install the New Bulb
instructions.instruction: Insert the new turn signal bulb into the socket until it clicks into place.

instructions.title: Reinsert the Socket
instructions.instruction: Place the socket back into the housing and twist it clockwise to secure it.

instructions.title: Test the Turn Signal
instructions.instruction: Turn on the vehicle and activate the turn signal to ensure itÆs working properly.

instructions.title: Turn Off the Engine
instructions.instruction: Ensure the vehicle is parked, turned off, and the key is removed from the ignition.

instructions.title: Open the Hood
instructions.instruction: Release the hood latch and lift the hood. Use the prop rod if necessary to hold it open.

instructions.title: Locate the Air Filter Housing
instructions.instruction: Find the air filter housing ù typically a rectangular black box with clips or screws, usually near the top of the engine.

instructions.title: Open the Housing
instructions.instruction: Unclip or unscrew the air filter housing cover and lift it to expose the air filter inside.

instructions.title: Remove the Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Take out the old air filter and inspect the housing for dirt or debris. Wipe it clean with a dry cloth if needed.

instructions.title: Insert the New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place the new air filter in the same orientation as the old one. Make sure it fits snugly and seals properly.

instructions.title: Close the Housing
instructions.instruction: Reattach the housing cover by snapping the clips back into place or tightening the screws.

instructions.title: Close the Hood
instructions.instruction: Lower the hood and ensure it is securely latched.

instructions.title: Turn Off the Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Ensure the engine is off and the keys are removed from the ignition.

instructions.title: Open the Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Open the glove box and remove any contents to prevent obstruction during the process.

instructions.title: Detach the Glove Box Stops
instructions.instruction: Locate the side stoppers inside the glove box. Gently press in on the sides of the glove box to release the stops and allow it to hang freely.

instructions.title: Locate the Cabin Air Filter Cover
instructions.instruction: Behind the glove box, you should see a rectangular plastic coverùthis protects the cabin air filter.

instructions.title: Remove the Filter Cover
instructions.instruction: Press the tabs or unscrew the cover to remove it and expose the old cabin air filter.

instructions.title: Take Out the Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Slide the old filter straight out, paying attention to the airflow direction arrows printed on it.

instructions.title: Install the New Filter
instructions.instruction: Insert the new cabin air filter in the same orientation as the old one, making sure the airflow arrows point in the correct direction.

instructions.title: Reinstall the Cover and Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Snap the filter cover back into place and gently lift and push the glove box back into its tracks until it clicks into place.

instructions.title: Turn Off the Engine
instructions.instruction: Ensure the engine is completely off and remove the keys from the ignition. Engage the parking brake.

instructions.title: Open the Hood
instructions.instruction: Pull the hood release lever inside the car, then open the hood and secure it with the prop rod if needed.

instructions.title: Locate the Battery
instructions.instruction: Find the batteryùusually located on either side of the engine bay, in a plastic housing or tray.

instructions.title: Disconnect the Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Using a wrench, loosen the nut on the negative (-) battery terminal and remove the cable. Move it aside to prevent contact.

instructions.title: Disconnect the Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen the nut on the positive (+) terminal and remove the cable. Avoid touching any metal with the wrench.

instructions.title: Remove Battery Hold-Down Clamp
instructions.instruction: If the battery is secured with a bracket or clamp, remove it using a socket or wrench.

instructions.title: Remove the Old Battery
instructions.instruction: Lift the battery straight out using both hands. Batteries are heavyùuse proper lifting technique.

instructions.title: Clean the Terminals (Optional)
instructions.instruction: Use a wire brush or terminal cleaner to remove any corrosion from the cable ends and battery tray.

instructions.title: Install the New Battery
instructions.instruction: Place the new battery into the tray with terminals in the same orientation. Reinstall the hold-down clamp if applicable.

instructions.title: Reconnect the Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach and tighten the positive (+) battery cable first.

instructions.title: Reconnect the Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach and tighten the negative (-) cable last.

instructions.title: Close the Hood and Start the Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Ensure all tools are removed from the engine bay. Close the hood securely and start the engine to confirm the battery is functioning.

instructions.title: Gather Tools and Supplies
instructions.instruction: You'll need engine oil (refer to owner's manual, e.g., 5W-30 synthetic), a new oil filter, a wrench or socket set, an oil filter wrench, a funnel, a drain pan, gloves, and rags.

instructions.title: Warm Up the Engine
instructions.instruction: Run the engine for 5û10 minutes to warm the oil. This helps it drain more easily. Turn off the engine and let it cool slightly for safety.

instructions.title: Raise and Secure the Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Use a jack and jack stands or ramps to lift the front of the vehicle. Ensure itÆs stable and parked on a level surface. Engage the parking brake.

instructions.title: Place Drain Pan Under the Oil Pan
instructions.instruction: Locate the oil pan under the engine. Position the drain pan beneath the oil drain plug.

instructions.title: Remove the Oil Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Use a wrench or socket to loosen and remove the drain plug. Allow all the oil to drain (this may take 5û10 minutes).

instructions.title: Remove the Old Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Use an oil filter wrench to loosen the filter. Be prepared for additional oil to spill. Check that the old rubber gasket is removed with the filter.

instructions.title: Install the New Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Apply a bit of new oil to the rubber gasket on the new filter. Screw it on by hand until snug, then tighten it another ╛ turn (do not over-tighten).

instructions.title: Reinstall the Oil Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Once the oil has fully drained, wipe the area and reinsert the drain plug. Tighten securely but donÆt over-torque (typically 25û30 ft-lbs).

instructions.title: Add New Engine Oil
instructions.instruction: Open the hood and remove the oil filler cap. Using a funnel, pour in the correct amount of oil (e.g., 4.5û5 quarts of 5W-30 synthetic).

instructions.title: Check Oil Level
instructions.instruction: Wait a minute for oil to settle. Use the dipstick to check the level. It should be between the min and max marks. Add more if necessary.

instructions.title: Start Engine and Check for Leaks
instructions.instruction: Start the engine and let it run for 1û2 minutes. Check underneath for any leaks around the drain plug or filter.

instructions.title: Dispose of Old Oil and Filter Properly
instructions.instruction: Pour used oil into a sealed container. Recycle the oil and filter at an auto parts store or local hazardous waste center.

instructions.title: Reset Oil Life Monitor (if applicable)
instructions.instruction: Use the dashboard menu or button sequence (refer to your manual) to reset the oil change reminder light.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get 4.5 quarts of 5W-20 motor oil (0W-20 is also acceptable), a new oil filter (Honda OEM 15400-PLM-A02 or equivalent), a 17mm socket for the drain plug, a drain pan, funnel, oil filter wrench, and a new drain plug washer. Wear gloves and safety glasses.

instructions.title: Warm Up Engine
instructions.instruction: Run the engine for 5–10 minutes to warm the oil slightly, then shut it off.

instructions.title: Raise Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Use a jack to raise the front of the car and secure it with jack stands on level ground. Engage the parking brake.

instructions.title: Locate Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Locate the oil drain plug (17mm) on the bottom of the oil pan. Position the drain pan underneath.

instructions.title: Drain Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Remove the drain plug with the 17mm socket and let the oil drain completely. Replace the crush washer with a new one.

instructions.title: Reinstall Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Reinstall the drain plug with the new washer. Torque to 29 ft-lbs (40 Nm). Do not overtighten.

instructions.title: Locate Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Locate the oil filter. On the 2.4L I4 it’s mounted on the front of the engine; on the 3.5L V6 it’s underneath near the exhaust pipe. Place the drain pan beneath it.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Loosen and remove the old oil filter with a wrench. Expect some oil to spill out.

instructions.title: Install New Filter
instructions.instruction: Apply a thin coat of fresh oil to the new filter’s rubber gasket. Screw it on by hand until snug, then tighten an additional 3/4 turn.

instructions.title: Lower Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Carefully lower the vehicle back to the ground.

instructions.title: Add New Oil
instructions.instruction: Remove the oil filler cap on top of the engine and pour in about 4.5 quarts of fresh oil (check manual for exact capacity by engine type).

instructions.title: Run Engine and Check Leaks
instructions.instruction: Replace the oil cap, start the engine, and let it run for a minute. Check under the car for leaks around the drain plug and filter.

instructions.title: Check Oil Level
instructions.instruction: Shut off the engine and wait 5 minutes. Pull the dipstick, wipe, reinsert, and check the oil level. Add small amounts as needed until full (do not overfill).

instructions.title: Dispose of Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Pour the used oil into a sealed container and recycle it along with the old filter at an auto parts store or recycling center.

instructions.title: Reset Maintenance Minder
instructions.instruction: Turn ignition to ON. Press the Select/Reset knob until the oil life indicator is displayed. Hold it for 10 seconds until the oil life blinks, then hold again until it resets to 100%.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new 12V automotive battery (Group 35, ~550–650 CCA recommended), 10mm wrench or socket, battery terminal brush, gloves, and safety glasses. Optional: memory saver to retain radio presets.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off the engine, remove the key, engage the parking brake, and ensure the transmission is in Park (P).

instructions.title: Locate Battery
instructions.instruction: Open the hood and locate the battery. On the 2012 Accord, it is mounted in the engine bay on the driver’s side.

instructions.title: Disconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Use a 10mm wrench to loosen the nut on the negative (-) battery terminal clamp. Remove the cable and move it aside to prevent contact.

instructions.title: Disconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen the nut on the positive (+) terminal clamp and remove the cable. Move it aside from the battery.

instructions.title: Remove Hold-Down Clamp
instructions.instruction: Remove the battery hold-down bracket by loosening the bolts. Set it aside.

instructions.title: Remove Old Battery
instructions.instruction: Lift the old battery out of the tray carefully. Batteries are heavy—use proper lifting technique.

instructions.title: Clean Tray and Terminals
instructions.instruction: Inspect the battery tray and clamps. Clean any corrosion with a terminal brush or a baking soda/water solution, then dry thoroughly.

instructions.title: Install New Battery
instructions.instruction: Place the new battery in the tray with the terminals positioned the same way as the old one (positive on the correct side).

instructions.title: Secure Battery
instructions.instruction: Reinstall the hold-down bracket and tighten the bolts so the battery is secure but not overly tight.

instructions.title: Reconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach the positive (+) cable to the positive terminal and tighten the 10mm nut securely.

instructions.title: Reconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach the negative (-) cable to the negative terminal and tighten the 10mm nut securely.

instructions.title: Test Installation
instructions.instruction: Start the engine to confirm the battery is working correctly. Reset the clock and radio presets if needed.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Close the hood and dispose of the old battery at an auto parts store or recycling center.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new cabin air filter (Honda OEM 80292-SDA-A01 or equivalent) and a small flathead screwdriver if needed. Wear gloves to keep the filter clean.

instructions.title: Empty Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Open the passenger-side glove box and remove all contents.

instructions.title: Release Stopper Tabs
instructions.instruction: Locate the two stopper tabs on the sides of the glove box. Push them inward to allow the glove box to swing down further.

instructions.title: Detach Damper Arm
instructions.instruction: On the right side of the glove box, detach the small damper arm by sliding or unclipping it so the glove box drops fully.

instructions.title: Locate Filter Housing
instructions.instruction: Behind the glove box, find the rectangular cabin air filter housing cover. It has clips on both sides.

instructions.title: Remove Filter Cover
instructions.instruction: Unclip the latches on both sides of the housing cover and remove it.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Slide the old cabin air filter straight out. Note the airflow arrow direction printed on the side.

instructions.title: Clean Housing
instructions.instruction: Check inside the housing for leaves or debris and clean it if necessary.

instructions.title: Insert New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place the new cabin air filter into the housing with the airflow arrow pointing down, the same direction as the old filter.

instructions.title: Reinstall Cover
instructions.instruction: Reattach the filter housing cover and ensure the clips snap into place.

instructions.title: Reconnect Damper Arm
instructions.instruction: Slide or clip the damper arm back onto the glove box.

instructions.title: Reposition Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Lift the glove box back up until the stopper tabs engage, securing it in place.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Close the glove box and dispose of the old filter properly.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new engine air filter (Honda OEM 17220-R40-A00 for 2.4L or 17220-RCA-A00 for 3.5L V6, or equivalent). You may also need a screwdriver to open the air filter housing.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off the engine and ensure the car is parked on a flat surface with the parking brake engaged.

instructions.title: Locate Air Filter Box
instructions.instruction: Open the hood. The air filter box is a large black plastic box on the driver’s side of the engine bay (connected to the intake tube).

instructions.title: Release Housing Clips
instructions.instruction: Unclip the metal retaining clips (or remove screws if equipped) around the air filter housing.

instructions.title: Open Housing
instructions.instruction: Lift the top half of the air filter housing and pivot it open carefully to access the filter.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Take out the old engine air filter and set it aside.

instructions.title: Inspect Housing
instructions.instruction: Check inside the housing for dust, leaves, or debris. Wipe it clean with a rag if necessary.

instructions.title: Insert New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place the new filter into the housing, ensuring it fits snugly in the grooves and sits flat.

instructions.title: Close Housing
instructions.instruction: Lower the top half of the housing back into position and align it properly with the lower half.

instructions.title: Secure Housing
instructions.instruction: Reattach the clips (or screws) to secure the air filter housing tightly.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Close the hood. Dispose of the old filter properly.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get the correct replacement turn signal bulb (front: 7440/7440A amber, rear: 7440/7440NA amber). Have a flathead screwdriver or trim tool if panels need prying, and gloves to keep oils off the bulb.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off the engine, remove the key, and make sure the lights are off. Allow hot bulbs to cool before handling.

instructions.title: Locate Bulb Housing
instructions.instruction: Determine if you are replacing a front or rear bulb. Front bulbs are in the headlight assembly; rear bulbs are in the taillight assembly.

instructions.title: Access Front Turn Signal
instructions.instruction: Open the hood and look behind the headlight assembly. Locate the turn signal socket (usually the amber bulb). Twist and remove the socket.

instructions.title: Access Rear Turn Signal
instructions.instruction: Open the trunk. Pull back the trunk liner to expose the taillight assembly. Locate the turn signal bulb socket and twist it counterclockwise to remove.

instructions.title: Remove Old Bulb
instructions.instruction: Pull the old bulb straight out of the socket. Use gloves or a cloth to avoid skin oils if the bulb breaks.

instructions.title: Insert New Bulb
instructions.instruction: Push the new bulb firmly into the socket until seated. Do not touch the glass with bare hands.

instructions.title: Test Bulb
instructions.instruction: Turn on the ignition and activate the turn signal or hazard lights to check that the new bulb works.

instructions.title: Reinstall Socket
instructions.instruction: Insert the bulb socket back into the housing and twist clockwise to lock it securely.

instructions.title: Reassemble
instructions.instruction: For the rear, reposition the trunk liner. For the front, close the hood.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Dispose of the old bulb properly.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get the correct replacement wiper blades (Driver side: 26 inches, Passenger side: 19 inches, Rear wiper if coupe: 16 inches). Have a towel or rag to protect the windshield.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off the ignition. For easier access, turn the wipers on once, then turn the ignition off when they stop in the upright position.

instructions.title: Work on One Wiper at a Time
instructions.instruction: Lift one wiper arm away from the windshield until it locks into the service position. Place a towel on the windshield to prevent damage if the arm snaps down.

instructions.title: Release Old Blade
instructions.instruction: Locate the small release tab on the wiper blade where it meets the J-hook. Press the tab and slide the blade downward to remove it from the hook.

instructions.title: Attach New Blade
instructions.instruction: Align the new blade with the J-hook on the wiper arm. Pull it upward until it clicks into place. Tug gently to ensure it is locked.

instructions.title: Lower Wiper Arm
instructions.instruction: Carefully lower the wiper arm back onto the windshield.

instructions.title: Repeat for Other Side
instructions.instruction: Repeat the same process for the other wiper blade.

instructions.title: Test Wipers
instructions.instruction: Turn on the wipers to confirm they are functioning correctly and clear the windshield smoothly.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get 6.5 quarts of 5W-30 synthetic motor oil, new oil filter (Toyota OEM #90915-YZZD3 or equivalent), 14mm socket for drain plug, torque wrench (optional), oil filter wrench, drain pan, funnel, gloves, and rags.

instructions.title: Warm Up Engine
instructions.instruction: Run the engine for 5–10 minutes to thin the oil, then shut it off.

instructions.title: Raise Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Lift the vehicle front with a jack and secure it on jack stands on level ground. Engage parking brake.

instructions.title: Drain Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Locate the 14mm oil drain plug on the oil pan. Position drain pan, remove the plug, and allow oil to drain completely. Replace crush washer if worn.

instructions.title: Reinstall Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Tighten drain plug securely, torquing to 27 ft-lbs (37 Nm) if using a torque wrench.

instructions.title: Replace Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Remove old filter (driver’s side, below alternator). Apply fresh oil to the gasket of the new filter, install by hand, and tighten 3/4 turn past snug.

instructions.title: Add New Oil
instructions.instruction: Lower the vehicle. Open oil filler cap and pour in about 6 quarts of oil. Replace cap.

instructions.title: Run Engine and Check
instructions.instruction: Start engine for 1–2 minutes. Check for leaks at drain plug and filter.

instructions.title: Check Oil Level
instructions.instruction: Wait 5–10 minutes. Use dipstick to check oil level and top off as needed. Avoid overfilling.

instructions.title: Dispose of Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Recycle used oil and filter at an auto parts store or recycling facility.

instructions.title: Reset Maintenance Light
instructions.instruction: Turn ignition to ON, hold the odometer reset button until 'MAINT REQD' light clears, then turn ignition off.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a Group 24F 12V battery, 10mm and 13mm wrenches, terminal brush, battery protector spray, baking soda solution, gloves, and eye protection.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off engine, remove key, set transmission to Park, and engage parking brake.

instructions.title: Disconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen 10mm nut on negative (-) cable and move it aside.

instructions.title: Disconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen 10mm nut on positive (+) cable and move it aside.

instructions.title: Remove Hold-Down Clamp
instructions.instruction: Use 13mm wrench to remove the hold-down clamp.

instructions.title: Remove Old Battery
instructions.instruction: Lift the old battery straight up. Use proper lifting technique—it is heavy.

instructions.title: Clean Tray and Terminals
instructions.instruction: Neutralize corrosion with baking soda solution, scrub with brush, rinse, and dry.

instructions.title: Install New Battery
instructions.instruction: Place new battery in tray with terminals oriented correctly.

instructions.title: Secure Battery
instructions.instruction: Reinstall hold-down clamp and tighten firmly.

instructions.title: Reconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach positive (+) cable and tighten securely.

instructions.title: Reconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach negative (-) cable and tighten securely.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Start vehicle to confirm installation. Reset clock and radio presets if needed. Dispose of old battery at a recycling center.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new cabin air filter (Toyota OEM 87139-50100 or equivalent).

instructions.title: Empty Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Open passenger glove box and remove all contents.

instructions.title: Release Stopper Tabs
instructions.instruction: Push inward on both glove box side tabs so it can drop down.

instructions.title: Detach Damper Arm
instructions.instruction: Unclip the damper arm on the right side to fully lower glove box.

instructions.title: Locate Filter Housing
instructions.instruction: Find rectangular filter cover behind glove box.

instructions.title: Remove Cover
instructions.instruction: Unclip both sides of the cover and remove it.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Slide out old filter, noting airflow direction.

instructions.title: Clean Housing
instructions.instruction: Remove debris inside housing with a rag if necessary.

instructions.title: Insert New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place new filter with airflow arrow pointing downward.

instructions.title: Reattach Cover
instructions.instruction: Snap housing cover back in place.

instructions.title: Reconnect Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Reattach damper arm and push glove box up until tabs lock in.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Close glove box and dispose of old filter.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new engine air filter (Toyota OEM 17801-50040 or equivalent).

instructions.title: Locate Air Box
instructions.instruction: Open hood and locate large black plastic air box on passenger side.

instructions.title: Release Housing Clips
instructions.instruction: Unclip 2–4 retaining clips or remove screws as needed.

instructions.title: Open Housing
instructions.instruction: Lift top of air box upward to access filter.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Take out old filter element.

instructions.title: Clean Housing
instructions.instruction: Wipe out dirt or leaves with a rag.

instructions.title: Insert New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place new filter snugly into grooves in lower housing.

instructions.title: Close Housing
instructions.instruction: Align and close the top of the air box.

instructions.title: Secure Housing
instructions.instruction: Reattach clips or screws to lock housing in place.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Close hood and dispose of old filter.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get the correct turn signal bulb (front/rear: 7440 or 7440A). Have gloves to avoid touching bulb glass.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off vehicle and lights. Allow bulbs to cool.

instructions.title: Access Front Bulb
instructions.instruction: Open hood and locate turn signal socket behind headlight. Twist counterclockwise to remove.

instructions.title: Access Rear Bulb
instructions.instruction: Open rear hatch, remove interior trim panel or screws, and access taillight assembly. Twist socket counterclockwise to remove.

instructions.title: Remove Old Bulb
instructions.instruction: Pull bulb straight out of socket.

instructions.title: Install New Bulb
instructions.instruction: Insert new bulb firmly into socket without touching the glass.

instructions.title: Test Bulb
instructions.instruction: Activate turn signal or hazards to confirm function.

instructions.title: Reinstall Socket
instructions.instruction: Twist socket clockwise back into housing until secure.

instructions.title: Reassemble
instructions.instruction: Reinstall any covers, trim, or screws removed earlier.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get replacement blades (Driver: 22 in, Passenger: 21 in, Rear: 12 in if equipped).

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off ignition. Lift wiper arms away from windshield.

instructions.title: Protect Windshield
instructions.instruction: Place towel on windshield to prevent damage if arm snaps back.

instructions.title: Remove Old Blade
instructions.instruction: Press release tab on old blade at J-hook connection. Slide blade downward and off.

instructions.title: Attach New Blade
instructions.instruction: Align new blade with J-hook and pull upward until it clicks securely.

instructions.title: Lower Wiper Arm
instructions.instruction: Carefully lower arm back onto windshield.

instructions.title: Repeat Process
instructions.instruction: Repeat for other wiper (and rear if equipped).

instructions.title: Test Wipers
instructions.instruction: Turn on wipers to confirm smooth and proper operation.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get 6.0–7.0 quarts of 5W-30 synthetic motor oil (or 0W-30 for EcoBoost, check owner’s manual), new oil filter (Motorcraft FL-500S or specified type), 15mm socket for drain plug, torque wrench, drain pan, funnel, gloves, and rags.

instructions.title: Warm Up Engine
instructions.instruction: Run the engine for 5–10 minutes, then shut it off to warm and thin the oil.

instructions.title: Raise Vehicle
instructions.instruction: If needed, lift the front of the truck with a jack and secure with jack stands, or use ramps. Engage parking brake.

instructions.title: Drain Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Locate the drain plug on the oil pan (15mm). Position drain pan, remove the plug, and let oil drain completely.

instructions.title: Reinstall Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Install new washer if applicable. Tighten drain plug to 20–30 ft-lbs torque.

instructions.title: Replace Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Locate the oil filter (varies by engine, typically front or side of block). Use wrench to remove, let oil drain, apply fresh oil to new filter gasket, and install hand-tight plus 3/4 turn.

instructions.title: Add New Oil
instructions.instruction: Remove filler cap and pour in correct quantity of oil for your engine. Replace cap.

instructions.title: Run Engine and Check
instructions.instruction: Start engine, idle 1–2 minutes, and inspect for leaks around plug and filter.

instructions.title: Check Oil Level
instructions.instruction: Wait 5–10 minutes. Use dipstick to confirm oil level is between min and max. Add as needed.

instructions.title: Dispose of Oil
instructions.instruction: Recycle old oil and filter at an auto parts store or waste facility.

instructions.title: Reset Oil Life Monitor
instructions.instruction: On the steering wheel controls, go to Settings > Vehicle > Oil Life Reset. Hold OK until reset to 100%.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new 12V battery (Group 48/H6 AGM recommended), 10mm wrench, terminal brush, protector spray, gloves, and safety glasses.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off engine, set parking brake, remove key/fob, and open hood.

instructions.title: Disconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen 10mm nut on negative (-) terminal and move cable aside.

instructions.title: Disconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen 10mm nut on positive (+) terminal and move cable aside.

instructions.title: Remove Hold-Down Clamp
instructions.instruction: Loosen and remove hold-down bolt/bracket at the base of the battery.

instructions.title: Remove Old Battery
instructions.instruction: Lift battery straight up carefully. It is heavy—use proper lifting.

instructions.title: Clean Tray and Terminals
instructions.instruction: Clean corrosion with terminal brush or baking soda solution. Dry thoroughly.

instructions.title: Install New Battery
instructions.instruction: Place new battery in tray with correct orientation.

instructions.title: Secure Battery
instructions.instruction: Reinstall hold-down bracket and tighten bolt.

instructions.title: Reconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach positive (+) cable first and tighten.

instructions.title: Reconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach negative (-) cable last and tighten.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Start vehicle to confirm installation. Reset clock and radio presets if needed.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new cabin air filter (Motorcraft FP-92 or equivalent).

instructions.title: Access Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Open glove box and remove all items.

instructions.title: Release Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Press inward on both sides of glove box to release the stoppers and let it swing down.

instructions.title: Locate Filter Housing
instructions.instruction: Behind the glove box, locate the rectangular filter housing cover.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Unclip housing cover and slide out old filter. Note airflow direction arrows.

instructions.title: Install New Filter
instructions.instruction: Insert new filter with airflow arrows pointing downward. Ensure snug fit.

instructions.title: Reassemble
instructions.instruction: Reattach housing cover, lift glove box back into place, and close it.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new engine air filter (Motorcraft FA-1927 or equivalent).

instructions.title: Locate Air Box
instructions.instruction: Open hood. Air box is on driver’s side, near front of engine bay.

instructions.title: Open Housing
instructions.instruction: Unclip metal retaining clamps or remove screws holding the top cover.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Lift cover slightly and pull out old filter.

instructions.title: Clean Housing
instructions.instruction: Remove leaves or debris from inside housing.

instructions.title: Install New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place new filter snugly in housing with rubber seal facing upward.

instructions.title: Secure Housing
instructions.instruction: Reinstall cover and snap clips/screws securely.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get correct turn signal bulb (front: 7440A amber, rear: 3157A amber, check owner’s manual). Have gloves to avoid touching bulb glass.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off engine and lights. Let bulbs cool if recently used.

instructions.title: Access Front Bulb
instructions.instruction: Open hood, reach behind headlight assembly, locate socket, twist counterclockwise to remove.

instructions.title: Access Rear Bulb
instructions.instruction: Open tailgate, remove screws securing taillight, pull assembly outward, twist socket to remove bulb.

instructions.title: Replace Bulb
instructions.instruction: Pull old bulb straight out, insert new bulb firmly without touching glass.

instructions.title: Test Bulb
instructions.instruction: Turn on turn signals or hazards to confirm operation.

instructions.title: Reassemble
instructions.instruction: Reinstall socket, headlight cover, or taillight assembly as needed.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get correct replacement blades (Driver: 22 in, Passenger: 22 in, Rear: 8–9 in if equipped).

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off ignition. If needed, switch wipers on then off to leave them upright.

instructions.title: Lift Wiper Arms
instructions.instruction: Lift one wiper arm away from windshield until locked in service position.

instructions.title: Remove Old Blade
instructions.instruction: Press release tab on blade where it meets J-hook. Slide blade downward to remove.

instructions.title: Attach New Blade
instructions.instruction: Align new blade with J-hook, pull upward until it clicks. Tug gently to confirm secure fit.

instructions.title: Lower Wiper Arm
instructions.instruction: Carefully lower arm back onto windshield.

instructions.title: Repeat and Test
instructions.instruction: Repeat for other blade. Turn on wipers to confirm smooth operation.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get the correct amount of oil (typically 5.0 quarts of SAE 0W-20 full synthetic for 1.5L and 2.0L gas engines, or 6.0 quarts of dexos2 5W-30 for 1.6L diesel). Also have a new oil filter (ACDelco PF64 or equivalent), 15mm socket, drain pan, funnel, gloves, and rags.

instructions.title: Warm Up Engine
instructions.instruction: Run the engine for 5 minutes to warm the oil, then shut it off.

instructions.title: Raise Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Lift the front with a jack and secure on jack stands, or use ramps. Engage the parking brake.

instructions.title: Drain Old Oil
instructions.instruction: Locate the oil drain plug on the oil pan (15mm). Place the drain pan beneath and remove the plug. Allow oil to drain completely.

instructions.title: Reinstall Drain Plug
instructions.instruction: Replace the crush washer if needed. Reinstall plug and torque to about 18–20 ft-lbs. Do not overtighten.

instructions.title: Replace Oil Filter
instructions.instruction: Locate the oil filter (PF64, front underside of engine). Remove with a filter wrench, apply oil to gasket of new filter, and hand-tighten until snug plus 3/4 turn.

instructions.title: Add New Oil
instructions.instruction: Lower the vehicle. Remove filler cap and add 5.0–6.0 quarts of correct oil (depending on engine).

instructions.title: Check for Leaks
instructions.instruction: Start the engine, let it run 1–2 minutes, and inspect around filter and drain plug for leaks.

instructions.title: Check Oil Level
instructions.instruction: Shut off engine, wait 5 minutes, and check dipstick. Add oil as needed without overfilling.

instructions.title: Dispose of Oil
instructions.instruction: Recycle used oil and filter at an auto parts store or recycling facility.

instructions.title: Reset Oil Life
instructions.instruction: Turn ignition ON. Use steering wheel controls: Home > Info > Oil Life. Hold checkmark button until oil life resets to 100%.

instructions.instruction: Oil filter is a cartridge style, located under engine. Remove housing with filter wrench, replace cartridge and O-rings, lubricate new O-ring, and reinstall housing to 18 ft-lbs torque.

instructions.title: Add New Oil
instructions.instruction: Lower vehicle. Remove filler cap and pour in 4.8 quarts of 0W-16 oil. Replace cap.

instructions.title: Run Engine and Check
instructions.instruction: Start engine for 1–2 minutes, check for leaks around plug and filter.

instructions.title: Check Oil Level
instructions.instruction: Shut off engine, wait 5–10 minutes, use dipstick to verify level. Add oil if necessary.

instructions.title: Dispose of Oil
instructions.instruction: Recycle used oil and filter properly.

instructions.title: Reset Maintenance Light
instructions.instruction: Turn ignition to ON, use steering wheel controls: Settings > Vehicle Settings > Maintenance Reset. Confirm reset.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a Group 35 12V battery (AGM recommended), 10mm wrench, terminal brush, protector spray, gloves, and safety glasses.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off engine, remove key/fob, set to Park, and engage parking brake.

instructions.title: Locate Battery
instructions.instruction: Battery is under the hood on the driver’s side.

instructions.title: Disconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen 10mm nut and remove negative (-) cable. Move aside.

instructions.title: Disconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Loosen 10mm nut and remove positive (+) cable. Move aside.

instructions.title: Remove Hold-Down Clamp
instructions.instruction: Loosen bolts securing the battery hold-down bracket and remove it.

instructions.title: Remove Old Battery
instructions.instruction: Lift out battery carefully—it is heavy.

instructions.title: Clean Tray and Terminals
instructions.instruction: Clean any corrosion with brush or baking soda solution, then dry.

instructions.title: Install New Battery
instructions.instruction: Place new battery in tray with correct terminal orientation.

instructions.title: Secure Battery
instructions.instruction: Reinstall hold-down bracket and tighten bolts.

instructions.title: Reconnect Positive Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach positive (+) cable first, tighten securely.

instructions.title: Reconnect Negative Cable
instructions.instruction: Attach negative (-) cable last, tighten securely.

instructions.title: Finish
instructions.instruction: Start vehicle to confirm. Reset clock and radio presets if needed.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new cabin air filter (Toyota OEM 87139-58010 or equivalent).

instructions.title: Empty Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Open glove box and remove all contents.

instructions.title: Release Glove Box
instructions.instruction: Push in on both sides to release stops so glove box swings down.

instructions.title: Locate Filter Housing
instructions.instruction: Behind glove box, locate rectangular filter housing cover.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Unclip housing cover, slide out old filter, note airflow direction.

instructions.title: Install New Filter
instructions.instruction: Insert new filter with airflow arrows pointing down. Ensure snug fit.

instructions.title: Reassemble
instructions.instruction: Reattach housing cover and lift glove box back into place.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get a new engine air filter (Toyota OEM 17801-25060 or equivalent).

instructions.title: Locate Air Box
instructions.instruction: Open hood. Air box is on driver’s side near the front.

instructions.title: Open Housing
instructions.instruction: Release retaining clips or remove screws holding the top cover.

instructions.title: Remove Old Filter
instructions.instruction: Lift cover slightly, remove old filter.

instructions.title: Clean Housing
instructions.instruction: Wipe out dirt or leaves with a rag.

instructions.title: Install New Filter
instructions.instruction: Place new filter snugly in housing with rubber edge sealed properly.

instructions.title: Secure Housing
instructions.instruction: Reinstall cover and fasten clips or screws securely.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get correct bulbs (Front: 7444NA amber, Rear: 7440A amber). Gloves recommended to avoid touching bulb glass.

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off engine and lights. Let bulbs cool before handling.

instructions.title: Access Front Bulb
instructions.instruction: Open hood, reach behind headlight assembly, twist turn signal socket counterclockwise, and pull out.

instructions.title: Access Rear Bulb
instructions.instruction: Open liftgate, remove screws securing taillight assembly, pull assembly outward, twist socket counterclockwise, and remove.

instructions.title: Replace Bulb
instructions.instruction: Pull old bulb straight out. Insert new bulb firmly into socket.

instructions.title: Test Bulb
instructions.instruction: Turn on hazards or turn signals to confirm new bulb works.

instructions.title: Reassemble
instructions.instruction: Reinstall socket and secure taillight or headlight housing.

instructions.title: Gather Supplies
instructions.instruction: Get correct wiper blades (Driver: 26 in, Passenger: 16 in, Rear: 12 in).

instructions.title: Prepare Vehicle
instructions.instruction: Turn off ignition. Lift wiper arms into service position.

instructions.title: Remove Old Blade
instructions.instruction: Press release tab where blade meets J-hook, slide blade downward to remove.

instructions.title: Attach New Blade
instructions.instruction: Align new blade with J-hook, slide upward until it clicks. Tug gently to confirm secure fit.

instructions.title: Lower Wiper Arm
instructions.instruction: Carefully lower wiper arm back onto windshield.

instructions.title: Repeat
instructions.instruction: Repeat for other wipers including rear if equipped.

instructions.title: Test Wipers
instructions.instruction: Turn on wipers and washer fluid to confirm smooth operation.
